        <p><strong>VMware Inc</strong> is a U.S. software company that provides cloud and virtualization software and services, and was the first to successfully virtualize the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('x86', 'CPU'); ?> architecture.</p>
        <p>Founded in 1998, VMware is based in Palo Alto, California. In 2004 it was acquired by and became a subsidiary of EMC Corporation, then on 14 August 2007, EMC sold 15% of the company in a New York Stock Exchange IPO. The company trades under the symbol VMW.</p>
        <p>VMware's desktop software runs on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Windows', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?>, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X', 'OS'); ?>, while its enterprise software hypervisors for servers, VMware ESX and VMware ESXi, are bare-metal hypervisors that run directly on server hardware without requiring an additional underlying operating system.</p>
        <p>VMware website: <?php echo $this->stencil->addExternalLink('www.vmware.com', 'http://www.vmware.com/'); ?></p>
